text: University Housing monitors only the amount of traffic
Sony Playstation 2 is allowed by the University firewall
RHIT-OPEN will work in labs, classrooms and residence halls but does not allow the user to access the internal Rose-Hulman network
CounterStrike server is blocked by the University firewall
H323 video conferencing is allowed by the University firewall
CIS restricts traffic that is known to cause damage to the network or hosts on it, such as NETBIOS
These network security changes include blocking traffic from the Internet into the UW network over FTP
The network firewall does prevent some applications from working in their normal manner, for example, video and audio conferencing products that use the H.323
The individual will have a 4 Mbps bandwidth rate limit
MSN audio and video are not allowed by the University firewall, but the MSN chat, application sharing and file transferring are not blocked
No individual service or system running on the wired/wireless network should use more than 10 gigabytes of per day, regardless of whether it is inbound or outbound over the commodity network link
Battlenet is allowed by the University firewall
